subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes.
Head—body 100-120 mm, tail 68-78 mm, ear 19-22 mm, hindfoot 20-21 mm; weight 40-77 g. Dorsum of the Golden Spiny Mouseis reddish. Tail length is less than 85 mm, and soles, palms of feet, and hands are black. Tympanic bullae are more voluminous than in the Northeast African Spiny Mouse (
A. cahirinus
) or the Arabian Spiny Mouse (
A. dimidiatus
).
